sec.p:
Differences between the groups were compared using chi-square (χ
2
) test and Fishers exact test for categorical data and Mann-Whitney tests for nonparametric continuous data. The HIV RNA level was log10 transformed. Statistical significance was defined as P <.05. To assess the virologic outcomes, univariate analyses with a Cox model with 1 predictor was conducted. Thereafter, predictors associated with virologic failure at P <.10 in the univariate analyses were considered in the multivariate Cox proportional hazards regressions models. Persons who did not achieve virologic suppression by 48 weeks were censored at that time. All statistical calculations were made using PASW Statistics 18.0.2 (IBM Corporation, Somers, New York).
